gomodel:SYNGO_2413  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 2. Biochemical fractionation shows that LRRK2 and Rab5b co-localize at synaptic vesicles.\nLiteral:\n\"We found that LRRK2 was enriched in the soluble synaptosome fractions (Fig. 2, LS1 and LS2 of LRRK2) although it was also present in the cytosol and other membrane fractions (data not shown) as previously reported... Rab5 is known to associate with the membranes of synaptic vesicles as well as early endosomes [22]. Consistent with this, considerable amount of Rab5b was present in the soluble synaptosomal (LS2) and synaptosomal membrane (LP1) fractions. (Fig. 2, Rab5b). A synaptosome membrane marker, synaptobrevin-2, and a mitochondrial marker, Tom20, were not detected in the LS2 fraction, confirming that the LS2 fraction was not contaminated by the other membrane proteins (Fig. 2, LS2 of synaptobrevin-2 and Tom20). These results suggest that a fraction of LRRK2 and Rab5b co-localize at synaptic vesicles.\"\n\nFig. 3, Supplementary Fig. 2. LRRK2 and Rab5b co-localized at the presynaptic terminals.\nLiteral:\n\"In rat hippocampal primary neurons, LRRK2 and Rab5b were present in the cell body as well as along the neurites where they mostly colocalized with the presynaptic marker synaptophysin (Fig. 3Bii and iii) and with each other (Fig. 3Bi). Their localization at the presynaptic terminals was further confirmed by immunostaining with another presynaptic vesicle marker, synaptobrevin-2 (Supplementary Fig. 2). Taken together, our biochemical and immunocytochemical data indicate that LRRK2 and Rab5b are co-localized in neurons, primarily at the presynaptic terminals, suggesting that the interaction of LRRK2 with Rab5b\nmay have a role in synaptic vesicle trafficking.\". Experimental description: Hippocampal cultures from rat were used for the immunostaining, rat cortex for the biochemical fractionation were used.\nLiteral from M&M:\n\"E-18 primary rat hippocampal neurons were prepared as described [26].\"\nReference 26 used rat hippocampal cultures.\"\n\"Subcellular fractionation\nTo prepare the synaptosome fraction, rat cortex homogenates were fractionated as described [31,32].\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-09" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2413" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

